A vintage 1970s-style technical illustration showing a massive hourglass filled with flowing binary data (ones and zeros rendered as sand grains) sitting atop an old mainframe computer console. The hourglass is cracked and leaking streams of glowing data particles. Surrounding it are oversized vintage measuring instruments - pressure gauges, speedometers, and analog dials with needles in red warning zones. Coiled telephone cords and chunky ethernet cables snake around the composition like vines. The color palette features warm browns, burnt oranges, mustard yellows, and cream tones typical of 1970s technical manuals. The illustration style mimics detailed cross-hatching and stippling techniques from mid-century scientific diagrams, with a subtle paper texture overlay suggesting aged print material.
